OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781247870
OL,3,CDan Jarvis appointed as new Defence
OL,4,CSecretary
OL,6,FHe wrote: "My first duty is to keep
OL,7,Fthe British people safe, and I will
OL,8,Falways do what is necessary to protect
OL,9,Four national security.
OL,11,F"I am pleased to appoint Dan Jarvis as
OL,12,FDefence Secretary as we strengthen our
OL,13,Farmed forces and meet the growing
OL,14,Fthreats facing our country.
OL,16,F"This Labour government is delivering
OL,17,Fthe largest sustained increase in
OL,18,Fdefence spending since the Cold War.
OL,26,@nD@KOUsD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781247870
OL,3,CDan Jarvis appointed as new Defence
OL,4,CSecretary
OL,6,F"In a dangerous and volatile world, we
OL,7,Fwill give our armed forces the
OL,8,Fcapabilities they need to defend
OL,9,FBritain and keep our nation secure."
OL,11,FHealey resigned after a row with the
OL,12,Fprime minister over military spending,
OL,13,Faccusing the PM of making the country
OL,14,F"less safe".
OL,16,FHe wrote to Sir Keir Starmer to resign
OL,17,Ffrom the position with "great regret
OL,18,Fand reluctance", citing disagreements
OL,19,Fabout defence spending ahead of the
OL,20,Frelease of the delayed Defence
OL,21,FInvestment Plan (DIP).
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
